        width="364"
        height="108"
      >
      <p>
        Most Thread users visit Thread from their mobile devices, however
        internally we would always focus on the desktop design first because
        that’s where most orders were placed. How could we make the mobile
        experience the defining experience of the platform?
      </p>
      <p>
        We started by tackling this challenge by designing a native iOS
        experience of Thread and testing it with users. The prototype aims to
        replicate the native iOS feel as much as possible. The user’s feedback
        was positive and the team felt that a native app is the best way to
        experience Thread.
      </p>
