        Moving our product from being a website to a native application, done
        properly, required more planning. So we tried a different approach.
      </p>
      <p>
        We developed a new design system for Thread called Thread Whitechapel.
        This design system included new type styles, new touch interactions,
        new guidelines for flows and page content, and a new set of standard
        HTML components. This resulted not only in a better mobile experience,
        but it also allowed us to design and develop faster while keeping our
        visual language consistent.
      </p>
